Teizoku entered the Principal's office.
<???> Hey Tei!
(Mako?)
GendoSillhoutteAlt
josei_01b[BUST]
josei_01a[BUST]
Inside the office was the school’s Principal and
Teizoku’s long-time friend Mako, the student-body
president.
<Principal> Do you know why you are here?
<Teizoku> No Sir, I do not.
josei_04a[BUST]
The Principal eyed Mako. Mako smiled unconcerned.
<Principal> You were caught skipping class taking
pictures of our school’s rooftop garden. You thought
you sneaked away unnoticed, but the Janitor saw you
walk down from the roof.
Teizoku frowned, began to say something, but halted
at the wave from the Principal’s hand.
<Principal> Now, you know our rules are very severe,
we are an extremely prestigious academy.
<Principal> The rules state that you shall be given
a demerit and prevented from doing any extra-curricular
activities the semester, as well as informing our
sister universities of your unstellar conduct.
The Principal smiled and started toying with his
desk’s nameplate.
<Principal> Given that our sister university has the
best photography program in the country, this would
be unseemly towards your future.
Teizoku said nothing and gazed down-trodden at the
bushy carpet.
<Principal> I’ve also been informed by Mrs. President
that your rooftop garden photos ended up winning an
online competition, a decently-sized competition from
a local newspaper.
The Principal stopped toying with the nameplate and
gazed into the forehead of Teizoku.
<Principal> I have a proposal for you.
<Principal> Our school is in a regional competition
with our rival school, as you know the seniors are
tasked with winning it for us.
The Principal continued.
<Principal> This round of the competition is
photography, and the subject is local areas.
Our seniors are moderately competent here at best,
but we do not have a winning shot.
josei_04a[BUST]
<Principal> Mrs. President has informed me of your
talents earlier, and given that you wish to avoid
staining your reputation, it is my advisory opinion
that you take part as the anchor of the competition.
<Principal> My proposal is simple, take a winning shot
for the competition, if we win you will be absolved
of your crime.
<Principal> Moreover, I will personally put a good
word in to our sister University for your graduation,
seeing as you wish to have a photography career.
<Principal> If you don’t accept, you shall receive
the textbook consequences, including the stain on your
academic reputation.
<Principal> If you accept and fail us, you and Mrs.
President will both receive the demerits, since she
is the one who insisted upon this idea and spoke in
your good favor.
The Principal looked threateningly at Mako. Mako
looked unconcerned.
<Principal> Now, what is your answer?
<Teizoku> ...
<Teizoku> I accept.
Mako nodded happily.
<Principal> Good. Mrs. President will inform you of
the rest. Now leave my office both of you, I must
attend to important things.
Teizoku and Mako bowed their heads, and made their
way to the door.
<Principal> Do not fail me or you will regret it.
The Door slammed shut.
Teizoku and Mako make their way to an empty classroom.
A
bg_PrincipalOffice2
The Principal does not look up as Teizoku enters the
room.
GendoSillhoutteAlt
<Principal> Who is it?
<Teizoku> It's Teizoku.
The Principal looked up.
<Principal> I’ve been expecting you. Good of you to
get the message before you left for home.
<Teizoku> What do you want?
<Principal> The deadline is moved.
Teizoku froze.
<Teizoku> Huh?
<Principal> It is earlier now, in fact two days away.
I trust it will be of no concern.
Teizoku started jittering.
<Teizoku> Why is it so much earlier now?
<Principal> It’s a useful thing to prepare for in life
and business, deadlines are moved around all the time.
The competition commission does not need to provide
you a reason.
<Teizoku> Wouldn’t this inconvenience the other
participants?
<Principal> If you are a true competitor you make do
with what has been given.
<Principal> You are but a small fish to our pond of
academia, this arrangement fits the commission and
inter-school cooperation the best, even if the
athletes must adapt.
Teizoku simmered in silence for a moment.
<Principal> I trust that this will be of no concern?
Teizoku swallowed his exasperation, getting it stuck
halfway down his throat.
<Teizoku> I will make do.
<Principal> Good, now have a nice day. I have more
work to do.
Teizoku staggered out of the room with angry legs.
Teizoku went home.
A
The next day, the day of the deadline, Teizoku asked
Mako to come to the Principal’s office with him.
<Mako> So, you are finally here and ready.
<Teizoku> ...
<Mako> Took you long enough to come round.
<Teizoku> ...
bg_PrincipalOffice2
GendoSillhoutteAlt
josei_02d[BUST]
Teizoku entered the Principal’s office with Mako.
Mako and the Principal looked at Teizoku expectantly
for the photo.
<Teizoku> I don’t have the photo and I refuse to take
part in this competition.
josei_02e[BUST]
<Mako and Principal> Huh!???
josei_02b[BUST]
<Teizoku> You heard me, I quit. Do with my reputation
what you will, I don’t care. I’m not taking it.
<Mako> How could you?
<Principal> Teizoku, I have offered you grace and
amnesty in a situation where you should’ve been
condemned, and this is how you treat me?
<Teizoku> Fuck you, I don’t want any of that. And fuck
you too Mako for putting me here.
<Principal> How dare you say that, you insolent brat.
The school’s reputation will sink down because of you,
everybody will despise you.
<Teizoku> Well fuck them too, I don’t like them
either. None of this is on me, both of you are at
fault.
<Principal> You may say that, but I will make sure you
live the full extent of total responsibility for your
actions here. Same for you Mako for bringing this
failure into our critical competition.
josei_02a[BUST]
Mako was silent but was intently observing both
Teizoku and the Principal.
<Teizoku> Mako, you can’t gaslight people into
situations they are not at fault in, and then blame
them that they should be considerate of other people
involved like this.
josei_04e[BUST]
<Teizoku> I have integrity unlike you people who only
scheme, and that dignity is worth destroying my career
and reputation over.
<Teizoku> So fuck you all. Principal, you are caught
up in this mess, but I don’t care what happens to you.
<Mako> Hoh hoh hoh...
<Principal> You were the one to accept this
competition, and you were the one who got caught
skipping class, you’ve failed here and are completely
in the wrong.
<Teizoku> But Mako and you threatened me into the
corner here, so there is no moral responsibility in
accepting and fulfilling a contract signed at
knife-point.
josei_02d[BUST]
<Teizoku> And if it’s a crime to take photos on the
rooftop, then condemn and blacklist me already.
<Principal> You truly are a rotten child. The
legalities of this world do not work like that, you
will now be punished by the full extent of the law.
<Principal> You should be ashamed of yourself, how
many people have you let down with your decision here?
<Principal> You will be suspended now, you will be
blacklisted now, you will be prevented from any
extra-curricular activities now, and your failure will
be made known to everyone.
josei_03c[BUST]
<Principal> Mako, you stay behind and we will have a
talk.
<Principal> Get out of my sight Teizoku.
<Mako> Hope you made the right choice Tei-kun.
<Teizoku> Have a nice week both of you.
Teizoku walked out of the office.

<Mako> You waited up till the deadline eh?
<Teizoku> ...

<Principal> Thank you for your photo Teizoku. Your

josei_05b[BUST]
<Mako> You see Teizoku? Everything works out when you
listen to me.
<Teizoku> ...
<Principal> You both may go, we will celebrate in a
week’s time when the results are announced. The whole

Teizoku and Mako left the room.

school sized
josei_01b[BUST]
A week later, the commission announced the winner of
the competition was Shitake highschool, Teizoku and
Mako’s school. The winning pictures were published
both in the local and digital newspapers online.
Teizoku and Mako both became mini-celebrities in their
classes, and the praises, adulations, and envy from
the other students poured out non-stop.
To escape from all of the festivities, Teizoku and
Mako find themselves sitting in an empty classroom
once again.
<Mako> Your future and career as a professional
photographer are secured now,
josei_01b[BUST]
josei_04b[BUST]
<Mako> you are basically guaranteed internships at the
biggest journalism outlets inside the sister
University’s photography department.
<Mako> Liven up, everybody is celebrating you, you’ve
made all of this possible Teizoku.
<Teizoku> ...
josei_01c[BUST]
<Mako> You already submitted the photo, why are still
thinking about things? Can’t you see everybody
celebrating around you?
josei_01d[BUST]
<Teizoku> I have to go back to the cafe.
josei_01d[BUST]
<Mako> Why Teizoku?
josei_04a[BUST]
<Teizoku> For closure.
<Mako> It's not necessary, but do whatever you want.
You earned the right to do it.
<Teizoku> ...
Teizoku left Mako in the classroom.

<Teizoku> I have to go home Mako.
<Mako> The school’s not over yet.
<Teizoku> I have to.
josei_01c[BUST]
<Mako> Ah, wait a sec Teizoku.
Teizoku didn’t listen and left the building.
bg_trashbin
At home, Teizoku took Maiya’s tickets and threw them
into the trashbin. He packed up some supplies into his
backpack, and set off for the Shinjuku slums.

<Principal> The deadline is moved to two days away.
<Teizoku> Okay, okay okay. I got it, no problem.
I have to go.
Before the Principal could say anything, Teizoku ran
and staggered out of the room, shutting the door behind
him.
bg_hallway
Teizoku bent over and violently puked all over the
hallway.
<Teizoku> (What a trip that was! Maiya didn’t mention
it would be such a ride. Ugh, I don’t want to
experience that again! So is today really the day I
met Maiya? I’m really back in the past am I?)
Teizoku accosted a nearby student who just turned the
corner into the hallway and looked frightened at the
newly formed steaming pile of vomit next to Teizoku.
Teizoku confirmed with the student that the date was
indeed the past.
<Teizoku> (Okay, so I met Maiya tonight at the bridge,
but this time I’m supposed to go to the nearby alley.
I will live the rest of day until that time normally.)
Teizoku spent the rest of his day like he did his
first time through.
